<unittitle>Matron and sisters at the Salvation Army Hillcrest maternity home, North Fremantle, with some new arrivals</unittitle>
<unitdate>15 February 1945</unitdate>
<abstract>This photograph is from an article in the <span style="font-style:italic">Western Mail</span> which is held on the National Library's website, 'Trove'. It shows some of the newborn babies at Hillcrest, the Salvation Army's maternity hospital in North Fremantle. Many of the babies born to 'unmarried mothers' at Hillcrest were adopted.</abstract>
